*planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r4 (07 Jan 2004)

  07 Jan 2004; <plasmaroo@gentoo.org> planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r4.ebuild:
  Added patches to address the security vulnerabilities in bugs #37292 and
  #37317 and bumped to -r4.

  02 Dec 2003; <nerdboy@gentoo.org> planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r3.ebuild:
  Updated to -r3 and bumped to 'x86' for the 'do_brk' exploit patch.

  01 Dec 2003; Brian Jackson <iggy@gentoo.org>
  planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r1.ebuild,
  planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r2.ebuild, planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21.ebuild,
  files/do_brk_fix.patch: Fix 'do_brk' vulnerability.

  23 Nov 2003; <nerdboy@gentoo.org> planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r2.ebuild:
  Switched to the 'rpm' eclass.

*planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r1 (30 Oct 2003)

  30 Oct 2003; <nerdboy@gentoo.org> planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21-r1.ebuild:
  Added RedHat kernel.h file due to troubles with ScrollLock.

  18 Oct 2003; <nerdboy@gentoo.org> planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21.ebuild:
  Bumped to 'x86' since it now works with Alsa 0.9.6 or better

*planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21 (20 Sep 2003)

  20 Sep 2003; <nerdboy@gentoo.org> planet-ccrma-sources-2.4.21.ebuild:
  Added missing ACPI headers but this still has ALSA unresolved symbol errors.

  18 Sep 2003; <nerdboy@gentoo.org> :
  New Planet CCRMA kernel sources...

